Society</em>, London.</li>

<li>Finkelman, P., 1994, &ldquo;Thomas Jefferson and Antislavery: The
Myth Goes On&rdquo;, <em>The Virginia Magazine of History and
Biography</em>, 102(2): 193&ndash;228.</li>

<li>Gaustad, E.S., 1984, &ldquo;Religion&rdquo;, in Peterson 1984:
277&ndash;93.</li>

<li>Gish, D., and D. Klinghard, 2017, <em>Thomas Jefferson and the
Science of Republican Government: A Political Biography of Notes on
the State of Virginia</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University
Press.</li>

<li>Goldsmith, O., 1774, <em>An History of the Earth, and Animated
Nature</em>, 8 vols., Philadelphia: Edward Poole, 1823.</li>

<li>Greene, J.C., 1958, &ldquo;Science and the Public in the Age of
Jefferson&rdquo;, <em>Isis</em>, 49(1): 13&ndash;25.</li>

<li>Gutzman, K.R.C., 2017, <em>Thomas Jefferson, Revolutionary: A
Radical&rsquo;s Struggle to Remake America</em>, New York: St.
Martin&rsquo;s Press</li>

<li>Helo, A., 2013, <em>Thomas Jefferson&rsquo;s Ethics and the
Politics of Human Progress</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University
Press.</li>

<li>Helv&eacute;tius, C.A., 1810, <em>Treatise on Man: His
Intellectual Faculties and his Education</em>, W. Hooper, M.D.
(trans.), London: Albion Press.</li>

<li>Holowchak, M.A.,&nbsp;2014a, <em>Thomas Jefferson: Uncovering His
Unique Philosophy and Vision</em>,&nbsp;Amherst, NY: Prometheus
Books.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2014b, <em>Thomas Jefferson&rsquo;s
Philosophy of Education: A Utopian Dream</em>, London: Taylor &amp;
Francis.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017a, <em>Thomas Jefferson, Moralist</em>,
Jefferson, NC: McFarland &amp; Co., Inc.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017b, <em>Jefferson&rsquo;s Political
Philosophy and the Metaphysics of Utopia</em>, Leiden, The
Netherlands: Brill.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019a, <em>The Cavernous Mind of Thomas
Jefferson, An American Savant</em>, Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge
Scholars.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019b, <em>Thomas Jefferson:
Psychobiography of an American Lion</em>, Hauppauge, NY: Nova Science
Publishers.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019c, <em>Jefferson&rsquo;s Bible: Text
with Introduction and Critical Commentary</em>, Berlin: DeGruyter,
2019.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020a,<em>&nbsp;American Messiah: The
Surprisingly Simple Religious Views of Thomas
Jefferson,&nbsp;</em>Abilene: Abilene Christian University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020b, <em>Rethinking Thomas
Jefferson&rsquo;s Views on Race and Slavery: &ldquo;God&rsquo;s
justice can not sleep forever&rdquo;</em>, Newcastle upon Tyne:
Cambridge Scholars.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2024, <em>&ldquo;The Disease of
Liberty&rdquo;: Thomas Jefferson, Liberty, and History, A
Philosophical Analysis</em>, Wilmington, DE: Vernon Press.</li>

<li>Hull, G., 1997, &ldquo;William Small 1734&ndash;1775: No
Publications, Much Influence&rdquo;, <em>Journal of the Royal Society
of Medicine</em>, 90(2): 102&ndash;5.</li>

<li>Hume, D., 1755 [1987], <em>Essays: Moral, Political, and
Literary</em>, Eugene F. Miller (ed.), New York: Liberty Fund,
1987.</li>

<li>Hutcheson, F., 1726, <em>Inquiry into the Original of our Ideas of
Beauty and Virtue</em>, Wolfgang Leidhold (ed.), Indianapolis: Liberty
Fund, 2004.
 [<a href="https://oll.libertyfund.org/titles/2462" target="other">Hutcheson 1758 available on line</a>]</li>
 
<li>James, M., 2012, &ldquo;Race&rdquo;, <em>The Stanford Encyclopedia
of Philosophy</em> (Winter 2012 Edition), Edward N. Zalta (ed.), URL =
 &lt;<a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/win2012/entries/race/" target="other">https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/win2012/entries/race/</a>&gt;.</li>
 
<li>Jordan, W., 1969, <em>White over Black: American Attitudes toward
the Negro, 1550&ndash;1812</em>, Baltimore: Penguin Books.</li>

<li>Kames, Lord (Henry Home), 1758, <em>Essays on the Principles of
Morality and Natural Religion</em>, London, 2<sup>nd</sup>
edition.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1774, <em>Sketches of the History of
Man</em>, vol. 3, Edinburgh, 1813.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1798, <em>The Gentleman Farmer, being an
Attempt to Improve Agriculture by Subjecting It to the Test of
Rational Principles</em>, Edinburgh, 4<sup>th</sup> edition.</li>

<li>Kidd, T., 2022,&nbsp;<em>Thomas Jefferson: A Biography of Flesh
and Spirit,&nbsp;</em>New Haven: Yale University Press.</li>

<li>Konig, D.T., 2016, &ldquo;Thomas Jefferson and the Practice of
Law,&rdquo; <em>Encyclopedia Virginia</em>, Virginia Foundation for
the Humanities.</li>

<li>Kukla, John, 2007, <em>Mr. Jefferson&rsquo;s Women</em>, New York:
Vintage Books.</li>

<li>Lehmann, K., 1965, <em>Thomas Jefferson: American Humanist</em>,
Charlottesville, VA: University of Virginia Press, 1994.</li>

<li>Levy, L., 1963, <em>Jefferson and Civil Liberties: The Darker
Side</em>, Cambridge: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>Linn&eacute;, C. (Linnaeus), 1808, <em>A General System of
Nature</em>, vol. 1, William Turton (trans.), London: Lackington,
Allen, and Co., 1858.</li>

<li>Locke, J., 1690 [1964], <em>Essay concerning Human
Understanding</em>, A.D. Woozley (ed.), New York: New American
Library.</li>

<li>Magnis, N., 1999, &ldquo;Thomas Jefferson and Slavery: An Analysis
of His Racist Thinking as Revealed by His Writings and Political
Behavior&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Black Studies</em>, 29(4):
491&ndash;509.</li>

<li>Malone, Dumas, 1948, <em>Jefferson the Virginian</em>, Boston:
Little, Brown and Company.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1951, <em>Jefferson and the Rights of
Man</em>, Boston: Little, Brown and Company.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1962, <em>Jefferson and the Ordeal of
Liberty</em>, Boston: Little, Brown and Company.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1970, <em>Jefferson the President: First
Term, 1801&ndash;1805</em>, Boston: Little, Brown and Company.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1974, <em>Jefferson the President: Second
Term, 1805&ndash;1809</em>, Boston: Little, Brown and Company.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1981, <em>The Sage of Monticello</em>,
Charlottesville: University Press of Virginia.</li>

<li>Martin, E.T., 1952, <em>Thomas Jefferson: Scientist</em>, New
York: H. Schuman.</li>

<li>Marx, L., 1964, <em>The Machine in the Garden: Technology and the
Pastoral Ideal in America</em>, New York: Oxford University
Press.</li>

<li>Mayer, D.N., 2001, &ldquo;The Thomas Jefferson-Sally Hemings Myth
and the Politicization of American History: Individual Views of David
N. Mayer concurring with the Majority Report of the Scholars
Commission on the Jefferson-Hemings Matter&rdquo;,
 &lt;<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20111226091819/http://ashbrook.org/articles/mayer-hemings.html" target="other">available online</a>&gt;.</li>
 
<li>McColley, R., 1964, <em>Slavery in Jeffersonian Virginia</em>,
Urbana: University of Illinois Press.</li>

<li>McCoy, D., 1980, <em>The Elusive Republic: Political Economy in
Jeffersonian America</em>, Chapel Hill: University of North Carolina
Press.</li>

<li>McLaughlin, J., 1988, <em>Jefferson and Monticello: The Biography
of a Builder</em>, New York: Henry Holt and Company.</li>

<li>Merkel, W.G., 2012, &ldquo;A Founding Father on Trial:
Jefferson&rsquo;s Rights Talk and the Problem of Slavery during the
Revolutionary Period&rdquo;, <em>Rutgers Law Review</em>, 64(3):
595&ndash;663.</li>

<li>Millar, J., 1806, <em>The Origins of the Distinction of Ranks: Or,
An Inquiry into the Circumstances which Give Riser to Influence and
Authority, in the Different Members of Society</em>, Edinburgh,
4<sup>th</sup> edition.</li>

<li>Miller, J.C., 1977, <em>The Wolf by the Ears: Thomas Jefferson and
Slavery</em>, Charlottesville: University of Virginia Press.</li>

<li>Mirkin, H., 1972, &ldquo;Rebellion, Revolution, and the
Constitution: Thomas Jefferson&rsquo;s Theory of Civil
Disobedience,&rdquo; <em>American Studies</em>, 13(2):
61&ndash;74.</li>

<li>Montesquieu, 1758, <em>The Spirit of Laws</em>, Thomas Nugent
(trans.), London, 3<sup>rd</sup> edition.</li>

<li>Neem, J., 2013, &ldquo;Developing Freedom: Thomas Jefferson, the
State, and Human Capability&rdquo;, <em>Studies in American Political
Development</em>, 27(1): 36&ndash;50.</li>

<li>O&rsquo;Brien, C.C., 1996, <em>The Long Affair: Thomas Jefferson
and the French Revolution, 1785&ndash;1800</em>, Chicago: University
of Chicago Press.</li>

<li>Onuf, P.S. (ed.), 1993, <em>Jeffersonian Legacies</em>,
Charlottesville: University Press of Virginia.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007, <em>Mind of Thomas Jefferson</em>,
Charlottesville: University of Virginia Press.</li>

<li>Peden, W., 1954, &ldquo;Introduction&rdquo;, <em>Notes on the
State of Virginia</em>, in Thomas Jefferson, <em>Thomas
Jefferson&rsquo;s Notes on the State of Virginia</em>, William Peden
(ed.), Chapel Hill: University of North Carolina Press:
xi&ndash;xxv.</li>

<li>Peterson, M.D., 1960, <em>The Jefferson Image in the American
Mind</em>, London: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1965, &ldquo;Thomas Jefferson and the
National Purpose&rdquo;, <em>Proceedings of the American Philosophical
Society</em>, 105(6): 517&ndash;20.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1970, <em>Thomas Jefferson &amp; the New
Nation:A Biography</em>, London: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 1984, <em>Thomas Jefferson: A
Reference Biography</em>, New York: Charles Scribner&rsquo;s
Sons.</li>

<li>Risjord, N.K., 2002, <em>Thomas Jefferson</em>, Lanham, MD: Rowman
&amp; Littlefield.</li>

<li>Robertson, W., 1777/1855, <em>The History of the Discovery and
Settlement of America</em>, New York: Harper &amp; Brothers.</li>

<li>Sanford, C.B., 1984, <em>The</em> <em>Religious Life of Thomas
Jefferson</em>, Charlottesville: The University Press of
Virginia.</li>

<li>Scherr, A., 2014,&nbsp;&ldquo;Thomas Jefferson versus the
Historians: Christianity, Atheistic Morality, and the
Afterlife,&rdquo; <em>Church History</em>, 83(1): 60&ndash;109.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; , 2016, <em>Thomas Jefferson&rsquo;s Image
of New England: Nationalism versus Sectionalism in the Young
Republic</em>, Jefferson, NC: McFarland Publishers.</li>

<li>Sheridan, E.R., 1983, &ldquo;Introduction&rdquo;, in
<em>Jefferson&rsquo;s Extracts from the Gospels</em>, Dickinson W.
Adams (ed.), Princeton: Princeton University Press: 3&ndash;42.</li>

<li>Shuffleton, F. (ed.), 2009, <em>The Cambridge Companion to Thomas
Jefferson</em>, New York: University of Cambridge Press.</li>

<li>Sloan, H., 1993, &ldquo;&lsquo;The Earth belongs in Usufruct to
the Living,&rsquo;&rdquo; in Onuf 1993: 281&ndash;315.</li>

<li>Smith, A., 1759 [1982], <em>The Theory of Moral Sentiments</em>,
Indianapolis: Liberty Classics.</li>

<li>Smith, J.E., 1977, &ldquo;Philosophical Ideas behind the
&lsquo;Declaration of Independence&rsquo;&rdquo;, <em>Revue
Internationale de Philosophia</em>, 31(121/122): 360&ndash;76.</li>

<li>Stanton, L., 2009, &ldquo;Jefferson&rsquo;s People: Slavery at
Monticello&rdquo;, in Shuffleton 2009: 83&ndash;100.</li>

<li>Taylor, A., 2019,&nbsp;<em>Thomas Jefferson&rsquo;s
Education,&nbsp;</em>New York: W.W. Norton &amp; Company.</li>

<li>Temperly, H., 1997, &ldquo;Jefferson and Slavery: A Study in Moral
Perplexity&rdquo;, <em>Reason and Republicanism: Thomas
Jefferson&rsquo;s Legacy of Liberty</em>, G.L. McDowell and S.L. Noble
(ed.), Lanham, MD: Rowman &amp; Littlefield, pp. 85&ndash;99.</li>

<li>Turgot, A-R-J., 1750 [1973], <em>A Philosophical Review of the
Successive Advances of the Human Mind</em>, in <em>Turgot on Progress,
